{"article_id":"erd5JU9JxZ3A3aga","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Special Counsel Robert Mueller ' s report details ten \" incidents \"","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"in which President Trump sought to curtail or otherwise affect the direction of the investigation into Russian interference in the 2016 election .","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"Mueller ' s report outlines the president ' s attempts","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"to intervene in the special-counsel probe","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"to bring it to a premature conclusion","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"or to affect the public perception of it","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"by manipulating government officials ' statements .","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"It stops short , however , of making a prosecutorial determination","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"regarding whether Trump obstructed justice","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"- a decision","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"it indicates","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"is best left to Congress .","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"\" The incidents were often carried out through one-on-one meetings","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"in which the President sought to use his official power outside of usual channels , \"","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"the report reads .","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"\" These actions ranged from efforts","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"to remove the Special Counsel","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"and to reverse the effect of the Attorney General ' s recusal ;","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"to the attempted use of official power","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"to limit the scope of the investigation ;","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"to direct and indirect contacts with witnesses with the potential","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"to influence their testimony .","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"Viewing the acts collectively can help to illuminate their significance . \"","depth":4},{"id":23,"text":"The most prominent example of Trump ' s attempted intervention in the special counsel probe is his directing White House Counsel Don McGahn to remove Mueller .","depth":5},{"id":24,"text":"McGahn ,","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"according to the report ,","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"flatly refused to do so","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"and threatened to resign","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"rather than carry out the directive .","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"McGahn then refused Trump ' s directive","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"to state publicly","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"that he had not been ordered to remove the special counsel .","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"In another example","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"provided in the report ,","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"Trump urged then-attorney general Jeff Sessions ,","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"who had recused himself from the probe ,","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"to reassert control over it ,","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"telling the former Alabama senator","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"that he ' d be considered a \" hero \"","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"for doing so .","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"Trump also asked his former campaign manager , Corey Lewandowski , to ask Sessions to say publicly","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"that the investigation was \" very unfair \" to the president .","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"Lewandowski was uncomfortable with the task ,","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"so he asked another White House official , Rick Dearborn , to deliver the message ,","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"but Dearborn never complied .","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"In an effort","depth":6},{"id":46,"text":"to contain the fallout from the FBI ' s investigation into Russian contacts between his campaign and Russia ,","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"which gave rise to Mueller ' s investigation ,","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"Trump asked then-FBI director James Comey in January 2017 to stop investigating national-security adviser Michael Flynn ' s contacts with Russian ambassador Sergei Kislyak .","depth":5},{"id":49,"text":"Comey ,","depth":6},{"id":50,"text":"as he testified before Congress ,","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"refused to comply with that request .","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"Trump fired Comey shortly thereafter in part ,","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"as he later admitted ,","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"over Comey ' s refusal","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"to say publicly","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"that he was not personally under investigation","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"for colluding with Russia","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"to sway the election in his favor .","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"The reluctance","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"to follow Trump ' s orders","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"exhibited by Lewandowski , McGahn , and Comey","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"largely explains why Trump failed in his efforts","depth":7},{"id":63,"text":"to prematurely end or otherwise constrain the FBI investigation into his campaign ,","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"according to the report .","depth":5},{"id":65,"text":"\" The President ' s efforts","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"to influence the investigation","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"were mostly unsuccessful ,","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"but that is largely because the persons","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"who surrounded the President","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"declined to carry out orders or accede to his requests , \"","depth":7},{"id":71,"text":"the report reads .","depth":5},{"id":72,"text":"Attorney General William Barr announced Thursday morning","depth":4},{"id":73,"text":"that he and Deputy Attorney General Rod Rosenstein concluded","depth":6},{"id":74,"text":"based on the report","depth":6},{"id":75,"text":"that Trump could not be prosecuted for obstruction of justice .","depth":5},{"id":76,"text":"Barr based that assessment both on Trump ' s motivations","depth":6},{"id":77,"text":"for intervening ,","depth":6},{"id":78,"text":"which","depth":7},{"id":79,"text":"he said","depth":7},{"id":80,"text":"were not \" corrupt \"","depth":7},{"id":81,"text":"but rather stemmed from his frustration with the process ,","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"and on his interpretation","depth":6},{"id":83,"text":"of whether a president can be indicted for exercising control over executive-branch officials ,","depth":6},{"id":84,"text":"which ,","depth":7},{"id":85,"text":"he admitted ,","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"differed from Mueller ' s \" legal theories \" on the matter .","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":173,"left":131,"right":172,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":131,"left":98,"right":130,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":98,"left":88,"right":97,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":88,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":97,"left":92,"right":96,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":92,"left":2,"right":91,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":91,"left":3,"right":90,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":90,"left":4,"right":89,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":89,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"mode","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":96,"left":93,"right":95,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":93,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":95,"left":94,"right":11,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":94,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":130,"left":108,"right":129,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":108,"left":107,"right":22,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":107,"left":100,"right":106,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":100,"left":99,"right":14,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":99,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":106,"left":102,"right":105,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":102,"left":15,"right":101,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":101,"left":16,"right":17,"relation":"j